# session-manager-plugin GPG public key — REFRESH TEMPLATE
#
# The toolbox Dockerfile GPG-verifies AWS's session-manager-plugin .deb against
# AWS's plugin signing key (AWS publishes a detached .deb.sig alongside the
# package). This is a DIFFERENT key than the aws-cli one. The current key IS
# vendored in this repo as the colocated session-manager-plugin-key.asc — it's
# public, with its fingerprint documented in-file. This .example exists to
# ROTATE that key.
#
# WHEN TO REFRESH: AWS rotates the key (the vendored one, keyid 2C4D4AFF6F6757EE,
# has no expiry as published) — after which `gpg --verify` fails and the build
# breaks until refreshed.
#
# TO REFRESH the vendored key:
#   1. Open the AWS docs page "Verify the signature of the Session Manager
#      plugin" (Systems Manager User Guide, install-plugin-verify).
#   2. Copy the GPG PUBLIC KEY BLOCK shown there.
#   3. Overwrite  containers/toolbox/session-manager-plugin-key.asc  with it
#      (keep a short comment header documenting the new fingerprint + expiry).
#   4. Confirm  gpg --show-keys session-manager-plugin-key.asc  matches the
#      fingerprint AWS lists, then rebuild.
#
# (To build without a key — not recommended — pass --build-arg SMP_VERIFY=false.)
#
# -----BEGIN PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----
# ...paste AWS's published Session Manager plugin public key here...
# -----END PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----
